 The Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN) says it has reopened Runway 18R/36L, following the removal of Azman Air’s Boeing 737-500 aircraft with registration 5N SYS, and flight number ZQ2325 which was grounded in the middle of the runway, causing airlines to cancel flights on Tuesday.
The aircraft was said to have been removed in the early hours of Wednesday morning.
